  "instructions": [
    "Heat the sesame oil in the bottom of a clay tagine over medium heat.",
    "Add the ginger and garlic and cook until fragrant.",
    "Add the tendon and cook until browned on all sides.",
    "Add the oats, coconut aminos, and dry white wine, stirring to combine.",
    "Cover the tagine and bring the mixture to a simmer.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 2 hours, or until the oats are tender and the tendon is falling apart.",
    "Stir in the chopped green onions.",
    "Serve the tendon and oats hot, garnished with additional green onions if desired."
